se guilty of crimes against humanity. Whether he is directing Isabelle Huppert in The Sea Wall, following laborers digging trenches, or interrogating the infamous director of S-21 prison, aesthetics and ethics inform all he does. With remarkable access to the director and his work, Deirdre Boyle introduces readers to Panh’s groundbreaking approach to perpetrator cinema and dazzling critique of colonialism, globalization, and the refugee crisis. Ferryman of Memories reveals the art of one of the masters of world cinema today, focusing on nineteen of his award-winning films, including Rice People, The Land of Wandering Souls, S-21: The Khmer Rouge Killing Machine, and The Missing Picture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDocumentary filmszCambodiaxHistory and criticism. 0aGenocide in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  acambodia: between war and peace, rice people, bophana: a cambodian tragedy, one evening after the war, the land of the wandering souls, s-21: the Khmer Rouge killing machine, the people of Angkor, the burnt theatre, paper cannot wrap up embers, the sea wall, duch, master of the forges of hell, the missing picture.  aexile, first they killed my father, graves without a name, irradiated, cambodian film, cambodia, film history, human rights, the killing fields, rithy panh.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Pac